 :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">∏ <span class=\"fn\">a</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\">s</span>, <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span>)</span></span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">∏ <span class=\"fn\">b</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Image.html#Finset.image\">image</a> <span class=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\">s</span></span>, <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">f</span> <span class=\"fn\">b</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HPow.hPow\">^</a> <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">a</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\">s</span> | <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">g</span> <span class=\"fn\">a</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">b</span>}</span>.<a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Card.html#Finset.card\">card</a></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The product of the composition of functions `f` and `g`, is the product over `b ∈ s.image g` of\n`f b` to the power of the cardinality of the fibre of `b`. See also `Finset.prod_image`. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Algebra/BigOperators/Group/Finset/Basic.html#Finset.prod_comp","kind":"theorem","line":694,"name":"Finset.prod_comp","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/8f9d9cff6bd728b17a24e163c9402775d9e6a365/Mathlib/Algebra/BigOperators/Group/Finset/Basic.lean#L694-L701"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/BigOperators/Group/Finset/Basic.html#Finset.sum_ninvolution\"><span class=\"name\">Finset</span>.<span class=\"name\">sum_ninvolution</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">ι</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"imp